As seen from the inspection of subsets above, the consequent(s) of 100% confidence rules are ‘whole milk’ and ‘other vegetables’. This makes sense seeing that people, in general, consume milk and vegetables often. The consequent(s) of high lift rules include liquor, instant food products, rice, hamburger meat, wine, and popcorn among others.

The plot confirms what was stated above. Individual data points are shaded by confidence, and the most confidence occurs at low support and low to medium levels of lift.
